works.description: At last week’s Christie’s contemporary art auction in New York, Cindy Sherman’s 1981 photo “Untitled #96″ fetched $3.89 million, thereby setting a new record for the most expensive photograph ever auctioned. It was earlier expected to sell for between $1.5 million and $2 million. New York dealer Philippe Segalot bought the photograph, which shows the artist as a cashmere-clad ingénue lying supine on the floor and clutching a page torn from the newspaper classifieds.
